# ============================================
# DATA STORAGE OPTIONS
# ============================================

# OPTION 1: localStorage (Default - No setup required)
# - Works immediately, no configuration needed
# - Each user has their own isolated data
# - Good for: Individual learning, demos, testing
# - Limitation: Users cannot collaborate or share data

# OPTION 2: Supabase (Recommended for production)
# - All users share the same data in real-time
# - Enables collaboration between roles (Issuer → IB Advisor → CMA → SHORA)
# - Data persists permanently
# - Required for: Multi-user collaboration, production deployment
#
# Setup:
# 1. Create free account at https://supabase.com
# 2. Create a new project
# 3. Get credentials from Settings > API
# 4. Uncomment and fill in the values below:
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_project_url
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_supabase_service_role_key
#
# 5. Run SQL setup: lib/supabase/deploy-backend-integration.sql